  <span id="freeText12197265071834159175" style="display:none">"I'd gladly sell my soul to Satan for a year of freedom," cries Rosamond Vivian to her callous grandfather. A brooding stranger seduces her from the remote island onto his yacht. Trapped in a web of intrigue, cruelty, and deceit, she flees to Italy, France, Germany, from Paris garret to mental asylum, from convent to chateau - stalked by obsessed Phillip Tempest.<br /><br />Two years before <i>Little Women</i>, serialized in a magazine under the alias A.M. Barnard in 1866, this was buried among the author's papers over a century.</span>
