<div id="review_475455073" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/475455073" />
    <a title="Ava Catherine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8773670-ava-catherine"><img alt="Ava Catherine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1504048909p2/8773670.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/475455073?book_show_action=true">Dec 11, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ava Catherine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ava Catherine" href="/user/show/8773670-ava-catherine">Ava Catherine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780679445104" href="/book/show/1292100.A_Long_Fatal_Love_Chase">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8773670-ava-catherine?shelf=2015">2015</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8773670-ava-catherine?shelf=src">src</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8773670-ava-catherine?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer475455073" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16291685861752311260">Louisa May Alcott has always been one of my favorite authors, but in <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/620790.A_Long_Fatal_Love_Chase' title='A Long Fatal Love Chase by Louisa May Alcott' rel='nofollow noopener'>A Long Fatal Love Chase</a> we are introduced to a completely new Alcott writing style. She did not publish this book, which was written for magazine serialization, probably because it was considered too scandalous during her lifetime. This book is a romantic thriller that addresses women&apos;s issues important to Alcott. <br/>I found myself wondering if this was the kind of book Jo March might have written since it has all the elements of </span>
  <span id="freeText16291685861752311260" style="display:none">Louisa May Alcott has always been one of my favorite authors, but in <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/620790.A_Long_Fatal_Love_Chase" title="A Long Fatal Love Chase by Louisa May Alcott" rel="nofollow noopener">A Long Fatal Love Chase</a> we are introduced to a completely new Alcott writing style. She did not publish this book, which was written for magazine serialization, probably because it was considered too scandalous during her lifetime. This book is a romantic thriller that addresses women's issues important to Alcott. <br />I found myself wondering if this was the kind of book Jo March might have written since it has all the elements of her time period and is definitely written by a strong woman. <br />I love this book on many levels. It is a wonderful book about women's rights, and it is a treasure that was unearthed after many years among Alcott's papers, which she did not think would ever be published. It is a great romantic adventure. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16291685861752311260" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
