              <span id="reviewTextContainer2869200321" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14504671358078666781">3.5/4 stars<br/>I’m so glad my reading buddy and I decided to read this as a summer read. It is so different from any Alcott I have ever read before. High drama, and it really kept you on your toes. What was also interesting to pull out is how many themes really translate into our modern times. Friendship, dealing with abuse, things like that. I really liked our heroine Rosamund and appreciated how Ms. Alcott did not make light of the abuse Rose endured from the narcissistic Tempest, nor did she try </span>
  <span id="freeText14504671358078666781" style="display:none">3.5/4 stars<br />I’m so glad my reading buddy and I decided to read this as a summer read. It is so different from any Alcott I have ever read before. High drama, and it really kept you on your toes. What was also interesting to pull out is how many themes really translate into our modern times. Friendship, dealing with abuse, things like that. I really liked our heroine Rosamund and appreciated how Ms. Alcott did not make light of the abuse Rose endured from the narcissistic Tempest, nor did she try and make you sympathize with him at all. This is definitely not a first book of Alcott’s I would recommend to anyone, but if you’ve been reading her, I think you’d find delving into these serials she worked on very interesting.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14504671358078666781" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


